Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Largest piece of land located on Main Street

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: CBRE is pleased to exclusively offer the opportunity to acquire the 10.34 Acres located at 269 N Main Street, in Crossville, Tennessee. 269 N Main Street is the largest piece available in the Crossville town center. The property has 3 existing buildings – 16,000 sf – 9,588 sf – 1,995 sf- and can be subdivided into two separate +/- 5-acre parcels. Conveniently located in the city center, the property is primed for automotive, big retail or a mixed-use development. The property is located within close proximity to multiple residential communities and local businesses.

Adjacent to the tourist hotspot, Marathon Village
3-minute walk to the 32-acre mixed use Capitol View development. Home to HCA, HealthStream, Lifeway, multiple retail options, and over 1,000 apartments.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Marathon Village is a creative community of unique retail, business, entertainment, and more in Nashville, TN. It is a neighborhood born out of the buildings that once housed Marathon Motor Works (1910-1914) and is now home to American Pickers, Jack Daniels, and Harley Davidson.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: CBRE is pleased to offer for sale or lease, a two-story building with a unique interior space that includes dramatic high ceilings and brick walls. The property is located on the corner of Jo Johnston Avenue and 14th Avenue North in the Marathon Village community. Mike Wolfe, the star of the television shown “American Pickers” rescued and restored this 1880’s era Nashville building as part of Marathon Village’s urban revival.
